Practice Question 1: Product Not Found Exception
Problem

Create a Spring Boot REST API for products.

API
GET /products/{id}
Behavior

1️⃣ If id = 1 → return

Product Found

2️⃣ If id is anything else → throw a custom exception

Product not found with id: {id}
Requirements

You must create 3 classes

1️⃣ Controller

ProductController

Endpoint:

GET /products/{id}

If id is not 1, throw exception.

2️⃣ Custom Exception

Class name:

ProductNotFoundException

Extend:

RuntimeException
3️⃣ Global Exception Handler

Class name:

GlobalExceptionHandler

Use:

@ControllerAdvice

Handle:

@ExceptionHandler(ProductNotFoundException.class)

Return:

HTTP Status: 404
Body: Product not found with id: {id}

Use ResponseEntity.

Expected Output
Request
GET /products/5
Response
Product not found with id: 5

Status:

404 NOT FOUND
--------------------------------------------------------------
public class ProductNotFoundException extends RuntimeException{
    ProductNotFoundException(String msg)
    {
        super(msg);
    }
}
-------
@RestController
@RequestMapping("/product")
public class ProductController{
    @GetMapping("/{id}")
    public String findById(@PathVariable int id)
    {
        if(id!=1)
        {
            throw new ProductNotFoundException("Sorry product is not available");
        }
        return "Product found";
    }
}
-------------
@ControllerAdvice
public class GlobalExceptionHandler
{
    @ExceptionHandler(ProductNotFoundException.class)
    public ResponseEntity<String> productNotFound(ProductNotFoundException ex)
    {
        return ResponseEntity.status(HTTPStatus_NOT_FOUND).body(ex.getMessage());
    }
}
